<div type="definition">
<p>INTENSELY THICK so as to be UNABLE TO CUT.</p>
    </div>
<div type="notes">
<div type="old-chinese-criteria">
<p>[GENERAL/SPECIFIC]</p>
<p>1. The current general word for bluntness of any kind is dùn 鈍.</p>
<p>[GENERAL]</p>
<p>2. Cuò 挫 refers primarily to the act of making an object blunt.</p>
<p>[SPECIFIC]; [vt - caus]</p>
        </div>
